text.tspan: Annual change in atmospheric CFC-11 concentrations
Annual change in atmospheric trichlorofluoromethane (CFC-11) concentrations, given as actual measured
concentration change (solid line), and expected/projected rate of change based on reported emissions of parties to
the Montreal Protocol (dashed line). Since 2012, concentrations have fallen at a lower rate than expected,
suggesting unreported sources of CFC-11 emissions.
